WEBVTT

00:01.040 --> 00:03.562
[Horns honking in distance]

00:16.335 --> 00:22.921
♪♪

00:23.021 --> 00:29.568
♪♪

00:29.668 --> 00:31.690
[Spray-paint can rattling]

00:31.790 --> 00:39.858
♪♪

00:39.958 --> 00:48.067
♪♪

00:48.167 --> 00:56.235
♪♪

00:56.335 --> 00:58.077
[Protesters shouting]

00:58.177 --> 01:02.041
No justice, no peace!
No justice, no peace!

01:02.141 --> 01:06.245
No justice, no peace!
No justice, no peace!

01:06.345 --> 01:08.327
Woman: Traitor! Traitor!

01:08.427 --> 01:10.249
[Indistinct shouting]

01:10.349 --> 01:11.930
Judas!

01:12.030 --> 01:13.372
...no peace!

01:13.472 --> 01:15.414
No justice, no peace!

01:15.514 --> 01:17.856
No justice, no peace!

01:17.956 --> 01:20.019
[Voices fading]
No justice, no peace!

01:20.119 --> 01:22.261
[Indistinct whispers]

01:22.361 --> 01:24.483
[Door creaks]

01:34.253 --> 01:35.634
You doing this?

01:35.734 --> 01:37.976
Gives a whole new meaning
to "gun for hire."

01:44.102 --> 01:46.085
What does the state say
about bail, Ms. Motherwell?

01:46.185 --> 01:48.487
It's hard to imagine
a more egregious breach of trust

01:48.587 --> 01:50.569
than a serving
police officer

01:50.669 --> 01:52.851
beating a member
of the public to death.

01:52.951 --> 01:56.175
The accused is in an emotionally
fraught state of mind,

01:56.275 --> 01:57.896
which makes him
a real flight risk.

01:57.996 --> 01:59.858
Flight risk?

01:59.958 --> 02:01.740
We're all here right now,
Your Honour,

02:01.840 --> 02:04.663
because Officer Logan
walked into a police station

02:04.763 --> 02:05.944
to give himself up.

02:06.044 --> 02:07.386
He wants
to be here.

02:07.486 --> 02:09.788
My client wants
his day in court.

02:09.888 --> 02:12.711
How that makes him a flight risk
I have no idea.

02:12.811 --> 02:15.074
I got to say the state
is also concerned

02:15.174 --> 02:16.955
for the accused's
own safety.

02:17.055 --> 02:19.238
He's not safe, and you want
to put him in County?

02:19.338 --> 02:21.840
That's "Alice in Wonderland"
logic, Your Honour.

02:21.940 --> 02:25.204
A police officer at County
is a walking target,

02:25.304 --> 02:27.806
and this police officer,
under these circumstances --

02:27.906 --> 02:29.848
They're trying
to kill me.

02:29.948 --> 02:31.290
What was that?

02:31.390 --> 02:32.891
They're gonna kill me.

02:32.991 --> 02:40.979
♪♪

02:41.079 --> 02:43.021
$3 million D-bond.

02:43.121 --> 02:45.624
I'm assuming he doesn't have
the 300K up front, Counsellor.

02:45.724 --> 02:48.147
No, no, Your Honour.
Then I am entrusting
the accused

02:48.247 --> 02:50.229
to the safekeeping
of the fine men and women

02:50.329 --> 02:52.151
of Cook County
Sheriff's Department.

02:52.251 --> 02:54.153
[Gavel bangs]
Next.

02:54.253 --> 02:56.395
They got to her.
They got to her.

02:56.495 --> 02:58.076
Let's go.

02:58.176 --> 03:02.481
♪♪

03:02.581 --> 03:04.523
Uh, liquidate my pension.
Maybe, uh --

03:04.623 --> 03:06.245
M-Maybe a loan from
the patrolmen's credit union.

03:06.345 --> 03:07.566
Can you help me
with that?

03:07.666 --> 03:08.887
A police institution
getting a call from me?

03:08.987 --> 03:10.289
That's not gonna help, Logan.
How long?

03:10.389 --> 03:11.650
W-What?
Until the trial.

03:11.750 --> 03:13.452
We need more evidence.
We're not ready.

03:13.552 --> 03:15.134
How can I do that
while I'm in here?
What do you expect me to do?

03:15.234 --> 03:16.575
Come on, Logan, give me
something to work with!

03:16.675 --> 03:18.217
I don't know!

03:18.317 --> 03:20.259
Logan, you gotta give me
something to work with.

03:20.359 --> 03:22.541
You gotta give me
something.

03:22.641 --> 03:24.022
[Sighs]
Something.

03:24.122 --> 03:25.184
"Tweet."

03:25.284 --> 03:26.225
Tweet?
Let's go.

03:26.325 --> 03:27.266
Tweet.
One second.

03:27.366 --> 03:28.747
Leon Perkins.

03:28.847 --> 03:30.909
He goes by Tweet.
He's B-Brannigan's informant.

03:31.009 --> 03:32.651
He can corroborate the dirty
warrant, the drug bust.
He'll talk to me?

03:32.731 --> 03:33.992
And he definitely
has a record.

03:34.092 --> 03:35.354
You should be able to pull
his jacket,

03:35.454 --> 03:36.475
and can you do
something else for me?

03:36.575 --> 03:37.756
Can you stop
calling me Logan?

03:37.856 --> 03:39.478
Did you ever call
Moses Johnson "Johnson"?

03:39.578 --> 03:40.959
[Buzzer]

03:41.059 --> 03:42.641
[Cellphone chimes]

03:42.741 --> 03:46.205
♪♪

03:46.305 --> 03:47.686
Shit.

03:47.786 --> 03:51.049
♪♪

03:51.149 --> 03:52.811
♪ Chicago ♪

03:52.911 --> 03:55.814
♪ Where the dollar and
blue collar go hand in hand ♪

03:55.914 --> 03:58.257
♪ City of Dreams so big ♪

03:58.357 --> 04:00.579
♪ Nightmares don't stand
a chance ♪

04:00.679 --> 04:03.582
♪ A concrete paradise
where roses grow ♪

04:03.682 --> 04:05.224
♪ See the smile from a child ♪

04:05.324 --> 04:07.105
♪ Light up
the Magnificent Mile ♪

04:07.205 --> 04:08.947
♪ And melt the coldest snow ♪

04:09.047 --> 04:10.629
♪ This is home ♪

04:10.729 --> 04:13.151
♪ Find the brightest minds
on these dark streets ♪

04:13.251 --> 04:16.034
♪ See the heart and soul
on these old blocks ♪

04:16.134 --> 04:18.237
♪ Where we grow,
we call it the Go ♪

04:18.337 --> 04:21.340
♪ 'Cause we don't stop ♪

04:23.622 --> 04:27.286
[Police radio chatter]

04:27.386 --> 04:30.789
Your insurance will need this
for any claims.

04:37.075 --> 04:40.098
You know, I almost wonder
if you paid for this paint job

04:40.198 --> 04:44.503
to get the public attention
I know you crave so much.

04:44.603 --> 04:46.905
Who the hell do you think
you're talking to?

04:47.005 --> 04:48.587
You can pull that out there,
but you're not gonna

04:48.687 --> 04:50.869
come in here
talking to me like that.

04:50.969 --> 04:52.471
You know,
for two seconds,

04:52.571 --> 04:55.954
I thought you would pay for
what you did to Moses Johnson.

04:56.054 --> 04:57.155
But no.

04:57.255 --> 04:59.077
You still out here
being a bully,

04:59.177 --> 05:00.919
acting with impunity.

05:01.019 --> 05:03.642
The department refuses to cut
off the gangrenous limb

05:03.742 --> 05:05.724
no matter how much
you stink.

05:05.824 --> 05:07.406
[Door opens]

05:07.506 --> 05:09.768
But my community sees you.

05:09.868 --> 05:12.531
We're coming for you, and
we're gonna bring you down.

05:12.631 --> 05:15.053
Now get out of my office.

05:15.153 --> 05:16.295
Tell you what.

05:16.395 --> 05:19.177
We catch who did this,

05:19.277 --> 05:22.881
I know a lawyer who doesn't
give a damn who he represents.

05:26.405 --> 05:28.587
Frater: Hey,
w-what's impunity mean?

05:28.687 --> 05:30.629
You don't need to know
what it means.

05:30.729 --> 05:32.731
Counselor.

05:34.332 --> 05:36.515
Franklin:
What happened?

05:36.615 --> 05:39.037
David.
Dad.

05:39.137 --> 05:40.238
Look at what they wrote.

05:40.338 --> 05:42.361
Look what they said about Mom.
Scary!

05:42.461 --> 05:43.682
David.
Listen to Mom.

05:43.782 --> 05:45.243
David, go in the office.

05:45.343 --> 05:47.326
I'll be there in a minute.

05:47.426 --> 05:48.847
I'm coming, okay?

05:48.947 --> 05:50.949
I'm coming.

05:52.551 --> 05:55.173
Are you okay?
See what they wrote?

05:55.273 --> 05:57.055
See what they wrote?

05:57.155 --> 05:58.377
I-I'm sorry.

05:58.477 --> 06:01.300
Please, look at it.

06:01.400 --> 06:02.621
Look at it.

06:02.721 --> 06:05.744
Look at what they wrote.

06:05.844 --> 06:07.346
Look, look.

06:07.446 --> 06:08.587
Look, look.

06:08.687 --> 06:10.949
Look at what they wrote.

06:11.049 --> 06:13.051
Look at what they wrote.

06:15.614 --> 06:16.955
Why are you sorry?

06:17.055 --> 06:18.677
If I've done anything
to make --
Ugh.

06:18.777 --> 06:20.319
"If you've done anything."

06:20.419 --> 06:22.961
If -- If you've done anything
th-that -- that -- that, um...

06:23.061 --> 06:24.923
[Clears throat]
That's not sorry.

06:25.023 --> 06:27.646
Because if you were sorry,
you'd stop doing it.

06:27.746 --> 06:29.167
Right?

06:29.267 --> 06:31.910
And you're not gonna stop
doing it, are you, Franklin?

06:33.592 --> 06:36.415
[Sighs]

06:36.515 --> 06:38.256
You're hurting us.

06:38.356 --> 06:39.658
You know.

06:39.758 --> 06:41.820
It's -- It's the last thing
that I-I --

06:41.920 --> 06:43.502
Hurt you?
Hurt us?

06:43.602 --> 06:45.784
I-I -- Martha...
You know,
I-I think you think --

06:45.884 --> 06:48.827
I think you think there's --
there's conscience in this man.

06:48.927 --> 06:51.109
But it's not conscience.
It's -- It's guilt.

06:51.209 --> 06:53.632
But you call it conscience
because it --

06:53.732 --> 06:55.354
it's more noble
to call it conscience

06:55.454 --> 06:57.396
because it makes you
feel better for --

06:57.496 --> 07:00.359
for standing up for this
racist piece of shit!

07:00.459 --> 07:01.600
Martha.
What? What?

07:01.700 --> 07:03.241
You don't like
that language?

07:03.341 --> 07:04.723
Is that insulting?
Who are you?

07:04.823 --> 07:06.004
It's not about me,
Martha.

07:06.104 --> 07:07.606
Who are you?!

07:07.706 --> 07:10.369
You know, David could've
been here when this happened.

07:10.469 --> 07:12.010
You know that, right?

07:12.110 --> 07:13.692
He didn't sign up for this.

07:13.792 --> 07:16.094
You didn't ask me.
You didn't ask him.

07:16.194 --> 07:19.137
So if you gonna do this,
you're gonna do this
on your own.

07:19.237 --> 07:20.579
Us? No.

07:20.679 --> 07:22.681
W-What are you saying?

07:29.608 --> 07:32.130
[Sobbing]

07:36.815 --> 07:38.557
[Coughs]

07:38.657 --> 07:40.659
[Sobs]

07:46.224 --> 07:48.647
You got to stay away
from your family.

07:48.747 --> 07:58.657
♪♪

07:58.757 --> 08:00.619
[Clears throat]

08:00.719 --> 08:07.305
♪♪

08:07.405 --> 08:13.952
♪♪

08:14.052 --> 08:15.954
[David groaning lightly]

08:16.054 --> 08:22.080
♪♪

08:22.180 --> 08:24.402
Review Officer: Do you have
a history of mental illness?

08:24.502 --> 08:25.844
Johnny: No.

08:25.944 --> 08:28.527
Any family member have
a history of mental illness?

08:28.627 --> 08:29.968
No.

08:30.068 --> 08:31.450
Have you ever thought
about suicide

08:31.550 --> 08:32.851
or tried
to harm yourself?

08:32.951 --> 08:35.774
No, never.

08:35.874 --> 08:38.817
What gender
do you identify as?

08:38.917 --> 08:41.339
Um, I'm -- I'm --
I'm straight.

08:41.439 --> 08:43.582
Male, Irish.
Okay.

08:43.682 --> 08:45.784
Based on the information
the inmate has provided

08:45.884 --> 08:47.265
and other details
in his file,

08:47.365 --> 08:49.588
I'm recommending that he be
placed on suicide watch.

08:49.688 --> 08:52.471
Suicide watch?

08:52.571 --> 08:54.473
I'm not suicidal.
I-I just told you that.

08:54.573 --> 08:56.354
We're taking other factors
into consideration.

08:56.454 --> 08:58.356
You said "information
that the inmate provided."

08:58.456 --> 08:59.838
I didn't --
You have a right
to appeal this decision

08:59.938 --> 09:01.680
at your status hearing
14 days from now.

09:01.780 --> 09:03.802
Jesus Christ, 14 days?
Corrections Officer:
Let's go!

09:03.902 --> 09:05.083
Arms out.

09:05.183 --> 09:12.450
♪♪

09:12.550 --> 09:19.818
♪♪

09:19.918 --> 09:21.299
Hands.

09:21.399 --> 09:30.028
♪♪

09:30.128 --> 09:38.717
♪♪

09:38.817 --> 09:47.445
♪♪

09:47.545 --> 09:56.174
♪♪

09:56.274 --> 10:04.863
♪♪

10:04.963 --> 10:06.965
Nine inches.

10:09.327 --> 10:12.891
They say nine inches
in 12 months.

10:14.773 --> 10:16.394
Shoreline.

10:16.494 --> 10:20.799
Every year the lake eats away
at the city a little more.

10:20.899 --> 10:22.681
What's the word
for that?

10:22.781 --> 10:25.203
Erosion?
Yeah.

10:25.303 --> 10:27.305
Erosion.

10:28.586 --> 10:31.730
Logan.

10:31.830 --> 10:34.292
I had high hopes.

10:34.392 --> 10:37.375
We all did.

10:37.475 --> 10:41.379
Is this when you tell me
you've got this under control?

10:41.479 --> 10:43.501
I've got this
under control.

10:43.601 --> 10:46.905
♪♪

10:47.005 --> 10:48.667
Who was that guy?

10:48.767 --> 10:51.349
Canute.

10:51.449 --> 10:54.072
Crazy king who thought
he could hold back the water

10:54.172 --> 10:56.154
because he was royalty.

10:56.254 --> 10:59.277
Only everybody
gets the story wrong.

10:59.377 --> 11:02.200
Old King Canute wasn't saying
he could hold back water.

11:02.300 --> 11:05.563
He was saying
the opposite.

11:05.663 --> 11:08.887
"I'm only a king.

11:08.987 --> 11:10.969
The tide is the tide."

11:11.069 --> 11:13.051
♪♪

11:13.151 --> 11:15.774
This is Chicago.
It's a lake.

11:15.874 --> 11:17.135
Hmm?

11:17.235 --> 11:18.977
There is no tide.

11:19.077 --> 11:25.363
♪♪

11:26.725 --> 11:29.848
[Indistinct conversations]

11:36.134 --> 11:38.316
Hey, fellas.

11:38.416 --> 11:40.038
Is, uh, Tweet here today?

11:40.138 --> 11:41.279
Hey, you that lawyer.

11:41.379 --> 11:42.560
Which lawyer is that?

11:42.660 --> 11:44.002
Ayo, check it out.

11:44.102 --> 11:45.563
Ain't this the dude
from TV,

11:45.663 --> 11:47.886
repping the cop that killed
that brother in Bridgeport?

11:47.986 --> 11:49.367
-Yeah.
-That's him.

11:49.467 --> 11:51.049
Second ago, you was all about
Moses Johnson.

11:51.149 --> 11:53.051
Now you riding with twelve?
I'm still the same guy.

11:53.151 --> 11:54.733
I'm still looking out
for the neighbourhood.
That's why I'm here.

11:54.833 --> 11:56.614
Go on somewhere with that
slick talk, bro.
Listen.

11:56.714 --> 11:58.737
I'm -- I'm just trying
to find Leon Perkins --

11:58.837 --> 12:00.018
uh, uh, Tweet.

12:00.118 --> 12:02.300
Hey, Uncle Tom
right here.

12:02.400 --> 12:04.622
Lenny:
Everybody back up.

12:04.722 --> 12:06.705
Back up.
I got this fool.

12:06.805 --> 12:08.546
-Sellout, man!
-[All murmuring]

12:08.646 --> 12:10.148
Let's keep it moving,
old man.

12:10.248 --> 12:12.510
-This Oreo lookin' ass man.
-You better walk on.

12:12.610 --> 12:16.074
I'm looking for Tweet.
You know where I can find him?

12:16.174 --> 12:18.797
I saw the work you put in
for Moses.

12:18.897 --> 12:20.919
You saved that young
brother's life.

12:21.019 --> 12:24.803
Some superhero shit, for real.
Earned my respect.

12:24.903 --> 12:28.086
Which buys you one last favour.
Then you better be gone.

12:28.186 --> 12:30.248
Whatever you trying to do, you
need to keep it away from here.

12:30.348 --> 12:31.890
You feel me?

12:31.990 --> 12:33.972
Yes. Okay.

12:34.072 --> 12:35.533
Roseland.

12:35.633 --> 12:38.256
Three flat
on 107th and King.

12:38.356 --> 12:39.938
That's where
Tweet's girl live.

12:40.038 --> 12:41.820
Okay, thank you.

12:41.920 --> 12:43.301
Thank you so much.

12:43.401 --> 12:44.743
Ayo, ball!

12:44.843 --> 12:46.965
[Indistinct shouting]

13:04.582 --> 13:06.965
[R&B music plays]

13:07.065 --> 13:14.292
♪♪

13:14.392 --> 13:18.216
Uh, yes, may I speak
to the manager, please?

13:18.316 --> 13:20.098
Hey, how can I help?

13:20.198 --> 13:22.180
Hi, I'm Martha Roberts,
alderwoman of the fifth.

13:22.280 --> 13:23.701
This is my ward.

13:23.801 --> 13:25.904
Oh, well, I'm Charlie Patterson,
resident of the fifth,

13:26.004 --> 13:27.986
and this is my club.

13:28.086 --> 13:30.068
Okay, quick question
for you, Charlie.

13:30.168 --> 13:33.231
How are you gonna operate
without a liquor license?

13:33.331 --> 13:35.834
I don't understand.
Martha.

13:35.934 --> 13:37.435
It's Ms. Roberts.

13:37.535 --> 13:40.118
And you can't sell liquor
without my seal of approval.

13:40.218 --> 13:42.440
Oh, an actual seal?
Yes, actual seal.

13:42.540 --> 13:44.082
Like...

13:44.182 --> 13:47.285
♪♪

13:47.385 --> 13:49.287
...this?

13:49.387 --> 13:59.257
♪♪

13:59.357 --> 14:01.339
[Siren wailing in distance]

14:01.439 --> 14:07.946
[Muffled conversations, music]

14:08.046 --> 14:10.508
[Knock on door]
[Hip-hop music plays]

14:10.608 --> 14:15.553
♪♪

14:15.653 --> 14:16.795
Reynata?

14:16.895 --> 14:17.996
Who wants to know?

14:18.096 --> 14:19.237
I'm, uh --
I'm not a cop.

14:19.337 --> 14:20.598
I'm -- I'm a lawyer.

14:20.698 --> 14:21.840
S-Somebody die?

14:21.940 --> 14:23.942
I'm here to see Leon.

14:25.423 --> 14:26.965
Tweet.

14:27.065 --> 14:29.647
♪♪

14:29.747 --> 14:32.971
Y-You heard of, uh,
Moses Johnson?

14:33.071 --> 14:35.093
I'm the lawyer
who helped him.
Tweet needs help?

14:35.193 --> 14:36.574
He's mixed up
with some bad people.

14:36.674 --> 14:40.258
He may not know it now,
but he needs me.

14:40.358 --> 14:41.940
Tweet ain't here.

14:42.040 --> 14:45.543
♪♪

14:45.643 --> 14:48.186
It's important that
he calls me right away,

14:48.286 --> 14:49.868
as soon as possible.

14:49.968 --> 14:52.790
He's --
He's in big trouble.

14:52.890 --> 14:54.472
Thank you.

14:54.572 --> 15:03.601
♪♪

15:03.701 --> 15:05.283
[Exhales slowly]

15:05.383 --> 15:08.246
[Indistinct conversations,
telephone ringing in distance]

15:08.346 --> 15:11.769
[Clock ticking]

15:11.869 --> 15:14.893
Most of the time as a kid,
we were either dodging landlords

15:14.993 --> 15:17.555
or looking for
the next place to live.

15:19.757 --> 15:22.520
I just wanted a place
I could call my own.

15:28.046 --> 15:33.191
Give me everything you have
on Mason and his partners.

15:33.291 --> 15:35.293
And then you can leave.

15:37.055 --> 15:38.196
Should I clean out
my desk?

15:38.296 --> 15:40.298
Just go home, Marisol.

15:44.022 --> 15:46.024
[Door closes]

15:47.025 --> 15:48.566
[Sighs]

15:48.666 --> 15:50.948
[Train rumbling]

15:55.553 --> 15:57.976
Yo, little man.

15:58.076 --> 15:59.017
Get in here.

15:59.117 --> 16:01.819
TJ?

16:01.919 --> 16:03.921
Get in here.

16:04.362 --> 16:05.984
Look, it ain't nothing
to talk about, a'ight?

16:06.084 --> 16:07.425
You ratted on my brother.

16:07.525 --> 16:08.866
There's something
you need to know.

16:08.966 --> 16:10.708
What?

16:10.808 --> 16:12.790
You think Dante
got your back now?

16:12.890 --> 16:14.192
You think 'cause
you're affiliated,

16:14.292 --> 16:16.434
the Nation got you covered?
[Sucks teeth]

16:16.534 --> 16:19.037
Dante wanted Moses' ass
handed over to the cops.

16:19.137 --> 16:20.878
That's bullshit.

16:20.978 --> 16:24.302
What I got to lie for?
I ain't got nothing to lose now.

16:26.504 --> 16:28.886
TJ, why you even here?

16:28.986 --> 16:31.609
Cops made big-ass promises 'bout
how they was gonna set me up

16:31.709 --> 16:33.531
with a new life
after I testified.

16:33.631 --> 16:34.732
Okay, and?

16:34.832 --> 16:36.214
It reminded me of myself
tellin' you

16:36.314 --> 16:37.695
'bout Dante's plan
for Moses.

16:37.795 --> 16:39.577
It's both bullshit.

16:39.677 --> 16:41.179
I can't run.

16:41.279 --> 16:43.301
It's only a matter of time
before I'm six feet under,

16:43.401 --> 16:45.823
so I'm tellin' you
the truth right here.

16:45.923 --> 16:47.225
I owe it to you.

16:47.325 --> 16:48.987
Feel like I'm cleaning out
my soul a little.

16:49.087 --> 16:51.209
[Van door opens]

16:53.691 --> 16:54.792
[Door closes]

16:54.892 --> 16:57.195
Nothing,
he here for my mom.

16:57.295 --> 16:59.517
Him?
Trying to be my new dad, man,
I don't know.

16:59.617 --> 17:01.599
Yeah, I don't think so.

17:01.699 --> 17:03.041
What you talkin' about?

17:03.141 --> 17:05.083
That's a street cop
back in the day.

17:05.183 --> 17:07.805
Man, hell nah,
he a plumber.

17:07.905 --> 17:09.567
Nah.

17:09.667 --> 17:11.669
[Chuckles]

17:13.551 --> 17:14.973
You cappin'.

17:15.073 --> 17:18.736
You think I forget the face
of a man I put a bullet in?

17:18.836 --> 17:20.298
Alright, where'd you hit him?
Where?

17:20.398 --> 17:22.540
It was outside Lucky's
on Cottage Grove, bro.

17:22.640 --> 17:24.983
No, I'm saying like
where on his body, TJ.

17:25.083 --> 17:27.745
I was aiming
for the heart.

17:27.845 --> 17:29.587
Right?

17:29.687 --> 17:31.869
He turned last second.

17:31.969 --> 17:33.631
Bullet hit right here.

17:33.731 --> 17:37.275
♪♪

17:37.375 --> 17:40.158
Bro.
I'm a dead man walking.

17:40.258 --> 17:42.920
Just want to make my peace
with you before I'm gone.

17:43.020 --> 17:49.527
♪♪

17:49.627 --> 17:51.009
Phil:
Ask Franklin.

17:51.109 --> 17:52.810
What?

17:52.910 --> 17:55.853
Talk to the man.

17:55.953 --> 17:59.657
He, uh...
he respects you, Norma.

17:59.757 --> 18:00.858
No, no.

18:00.958 --> 18:03.541
Better still,
listen to him.

18:03.641 --> 18:06.024
I imagine he's getting a lot
of ear-wigging right now,

18:06.124 --> 18:09.687
and maybe what he needs
is just someone to talk to.

18:11.409 --> 18:13.391
What are we doing?

18:13.491 --> 18:15.313
What are we doing?

18:15.413 --> 18:17.395
[Sighs]

18:17.495 --> 18:19.757
What is this?

18:19.857 --> 18:22.720
I'm here.

18:22.820 --> 18:24.802
I'm here.

18:24.902 --> 18:26.524
I'm here.

18:26.624 --> 18:29.487
And I'm not going nowhere.

18:29.587 --> 18:32.650
I'm locked in.

18:32.750 --> 18:34.752
Okay?

18:36.474 --> 18:38.256
I'm here.

18:38.356 --> 18:40.138
I'm not going nowhere.

18:40.238 --> 18:42.900
♪♪

18:43.000 --> 18:45.863
So you gonna tell me
what else you love about me?

18:45.963 --> 18:48.186
♪♪

18:48.286 --> 18:51.109
[Both chuckle]

18:51.209 --> 18:53.791
You really want to know?

18:53.891 --> 18:55.713
Only if you want
to tell me.

18:55.813 --> 18:59.597
♪♪

18:59.697 --> 19:01.479
Think you'll make
a good father.

19:01.579 --> 19:05.243
♪♪

19:05.343 --> 19:07.345
What?

19:08.266 --> 19:09.927
Wait, really?

19:10.027 --> 19:12.009
12 weeks and counting.

19:12.109 --> 19:13.891
Oh, my God.

19:13.991 --> 19:17.735
Oh...
No, uh...

19:17.835 --> 19:20.418
This...

19:20.518 --> 19:23.781
Mm.
I -- I shouldn't...

19:23.881 --> 19:26.464
No, no, no, no.
Hm?

19:26.564 --> 19:30.428
Oh, my God, oh, oh, my God,
oh, my God.

19:30.528 --> 19:31.749
Oh, my God.

19:31.849 --> 19:33.591
Sure?

19:33.691 --> 19:35.072
Yeah?
Yeah.

19:35.172 --> 19:36.314
You sure?

19:36.414 --> 19:37.675
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

19:37.775 --> 19:39.757
Yeah.

19:39.857 --> 19:41.719
[Muffled]
I'm gonna be a father, me.

19:41.819 --> 19:42.960
Whoa!

19:43.060 --> 19:44.642
Yes.
[Kissing]

19:44.742 --> 19:45.883
Yes. Yes.

19:45.983 --> 19:47.125
[Sighs]

19:47.225 --> 19:48.966
[Door clanks]

19:49.066 --> 19:51.629
[Inmates shouting in distance]

19:55.353 --> 19:57.355
[Door shuts]

19:59.557 --> 20:01.139
Ugh!

20:01.239 --> 20:02.900
[Groans, spits]

20:03.000 --> 20:04.542
[Glass clattering]

20:04.642 --> 20:08.306
[Spitting]

20:08.406 --> 20:09.547
Ugh!

20:09.647 --> 20:18.115
♪♪

20:18.215 --> 20:20.398
Hey! Hey!

20:20.498 --> 20:21.999
[Banging on door]
Hey!

20:22.099 --> 20:30.308
♪♪

20:33.591 --> 20:42.380
♪♪

20:42.480 --> 20:51.349
♪♪

20:51.449 --> 20:53.030
[Sighs]

20:53.130 --> 20:54.872
[Knock on door]

20:54.972 --> 20:58.196
Just a minute.

20:58.296 --> 20:59.877
Coming.

20:59.977 --> 21:03.080
♪♪

21:03.180 --> 21:05.182
Be right there.

21:05.823 --> 21:07.965
Hey!

21:08.065 --> 21:09.647
Was in the hood.

21:09.747 --> 21:11.769
Thought I would drop by,
check in on you.

21:11.869 --> 21:13.451
Yeah,
appreciate it, man.

21:13.551 --> 21:15.553
Come -- Come on in here.

21:18.716 --> 21:21.219
[Chuckles]

21:21.319 --> 21:23.621
This is me.

21:23.721 --> 21:25.723
How are ya?

21:28.846 --> 21:30.628
When Moses was found
not guilty, it --

21:30.728 --> 21:32.750
it didn't feel like
the end of something.

21:32.850 --> 21:35.673
It -- It felt like
the beginning, you know?

21:35.773 --> 21:37.315
You know?
And this?

21:37.415 --> 21:39.637
I think I can get the people
who are trying to hurt us

21:39.737 --> 21:40.958
to look in the mirror,

21:41.058 --> 21:42.640
and for most of them,
it'd be the first time

21:42.740 --> 21:44.081
they've done that --

21:44.181 --> 21:48.125
if I can keep them there
looking long enough.

21:48.225 --> 21:49.767
You know the saying

21:49.867 --> 21:52.290
"you can't wake a person
pretending to be asleep"?

21:52.390 --> 21:53.971
I found a way in.

21:54.071 --> 21:56.374
I -- I can't stop now.

21:56.474 --> 21:58.336
Even if your family
suffers?

21:58.436 --> 22:00.258
Even if people suffer
because of you?

22:00.358 --> 22:04.662
I want my son to be safe
in his life

22:04.762 --> 22:07.545
and to feel safe.

22:07.645 --> 22:10.848
Now, that -- that -- that
would be a legacy, wouldn't it?

22:14.852 --> 22:17.415
What?
What's that?

22:21.058 --> 22:23.000
Joshua Johnson
came to me.

22:23.100 --> 22:24.201
Is he okay?

22:24.301 --> 22:26.804
To tell me
his mom is pregnant.

22:26.904 --> 22:30.608
And that the father
is an undercover cop.

22:30.708 --> 22:32.490
Oh, God.

22:32.590 --> 22:33.931
God.

22:34.031 --> 22:36.414
Does -- Does Norma know?

22:36.514 --> 22:39.156
No, he can't do it.
He won't hurt her.

22:41.559 --> 22:42.860
Good.

22:42.960 --> 22:44.261
Then we can use it.

22:44.361 --> 22:46.784
Wait, what are you saying?
Don't tell Norma.

22:46.884 --> 22:48.145
Joshua keep quiet.

22:48.245 --> 22:49.667
We'll play the cop
for all it's worth,

22:49.767 --> 22:52.390
and then, at the trial,
we'll roll it all out

22:52.490 --> 22:54.031
so everybody can see it.

22:54.131 --> 22:55.873
Wait, whoa, whoa.

22:55.973 --> 22:58.836
What are you doing?
This is Norma Johnson.

22:58.936 --> 23:00.678
Franklin.
She trusts you.

23:00.778 --> 23:01.919
She loves you.

23:02.019 --> 23:04.261
This is bigger
than all of that.

23:08.345 --> 23:09.687
[Banging on door]

23:09.787 --> 23:11.789
Unit Guard: Let's go, Logan.
You got a visitor.

23:13.791 --> 23:16.213
Nose bleed?

23:16.313 --> 23:17.855
Yeah.

23:17.955 --> 23:20.297
[Radio beeps]
Hazardous substance
release, 211.

23:20.397 --> 23:22.420
Copy that.
[Indistinct chatter]

23:22.520 --> 23:24.522
Let's go.

23:27.324 --> 23:29.266
[Buzzer]

23:29.366 --> 23:31.108
[Door slams]

23:31.208 --> 23:34.171
[Inmates shouting in distance]

23:58.075 --> 24:00.217
Are you okay?

24:00.317 --> 24:03.781
Um, yeah,
I'm -- I'm fine.

24:03.881 --> 24:05.062
I'm fine.

24:05.162 --> 24:07.545
[Inhales shakily]

24:07.645 --> 24:09.647
How's the baby?

24:11.328 --> 24:14.552
Uh, she's good.

24:14.652 --> 24:16.814
Michael Junior,
h-how's Michael?

24:20.297 --> 24:21.879
Michael doesn't sleep
at night

24:21.979 --> 24:25.843
'cause the man who killed
his dad is walking around, free,

24:25.943 --> 24:29.086
and he's like, "Well, what if
I bump into him, Mom?"

24:29.186 --> 24:31.308
How am I supposed to
answer that?

24:34.832 --> 24:38.055
And he saw Franklin Roberts
on a TV talk show,

24:38.155 --> 24:41.619
being treated
like a hero.

24:41.719 --> 24:43.060
And he can't fathom it.

24:43.160 --> 24:45.783
It's just --
It's upside down for him.

24:45.883 --> 24:47.425
And I tried to explain it
to him.

24:47.525 --> 24:50.708
I-I tried to tell him
that trials aren't always

24:50.808 --> 24:53.350
about the truth
and that lawyers are --

24:53.450 --> 24:54.992
are just guns for hire,

24:55.092 --> 24:57.314
and I-I think he understood
that, but...

24:57.414 --> 25:00.958
♪♪

25:01.058 --> 25:03.200
You.

25:03.300 --> 25:06.564
Uncle Johnny,
and the talk show lawyer

25:06.664 --> 25:09.286
who defended the man
who killed his dad.

25:09.386 --> 25:11.669
That doesn't work
for Michael.

25:14.111 --> 25:17.775
He can't make that work
in his head.

25:17.875 --> 25:20.137
And you know what?
I-I think he's right.

25:20.237 --> 25:21.819
[Inhales deeply,
sniffs]

25:21.919 --> 25:24.341
♪♪

25:24.441 --> 25:27.465
[Sighs]

25:27.565 --> 25:29.346
Here's the thing.

25:29.446 --> 25:32.309
♪♪

25:32.409 --> 25:34.351
It wasn't Michael Rossi

25:34.451 --> 25:37.314
that Moses Johnson
was running from...

25:37.414 --> 25:38.756
and fought with.

25:38.856 --> 25:40.958
♪♪

25:41.058 --> 25:42.840
It was the department.

25:42.940 --> 25:45.162
You believe that?
Yeah, I do.

25:45.262 --> 25:47.645
Well, then I need
to ask you something.

25:47.745 --> 25:49.286
The thing
that you did --

25:49.386 --> 25:52.650
beating a man to death
in public --

25:52.750 --> 25:54.532
was that the department?

25:54.632 --> 25:57.454
♪♪

25:57.554 --> 25:59.136
Or was that you?

25:59.236 --> 26:07.865
♪♪

26:07.965 --> 26:09.787
Hey.
How y'all doing?

26:09.887 --> 26:12.429
Alright.
Hey, lady.

26:12.529 --> 26:14.071
Alderwoman.

26:14.171 --> 26:17.234
[Indistinct conversations,
music playing faintly]

26:17.334 --> 26:21.559
♪♪

26:21.659 --> 26:23.240
Thank you.

26:23.340 --> 26:29.126
♪♪

26:29.226 --> 26:32.489
You come looking for me.

26:32.589 --> 26:35.492
Do I get my hopes up?

26:35.592 --> 26:37.535
I gotta say...

26:37.635 --> 26:39.176
the optics of
sittin' with you

26:39.276 --> 26:41.659
don't look too good on me
right now.

26:41.759 --> 26:45.983
Folks a little hurt
by what your husband's doing.

26:46.083 --> 26:47.665
Mr. Blake.

26:47.765 --> 26:50.347
♪♪

26:50.447 --> 26:51.989
Dante.

26:52.089 --> 26:54.111
Because a history
of employing children

26:54.211 --> 26:58.035
to sell shit to people
to fuck themselves up with,

26:58.135 --> 27:00.878
that's not a great look
either, is it?

27:00.978 --> 27:03.160
Well, you're here now.

27:03.260 --> 27:05.162
Now that you got that all
off your chest,

27:05.262 --> 27:06.403
maybe you can
tell me why.

27:06.503 --> 27:08.846
I need you to do something
for me.

27:08.946 --> 27:10.487
I need to know
who the players are

27:10.587 --> 27:14.892
that are selling sleet
through Club Fire.

27:14.992 --> 27:17.374
That's an ask.
I'm asking.

27:17.474 --> 27:22.900
Then it's a good time to get
a status update on my proposal?

27:23.000 --> 27:24.181
Mm.

27:24.281 --> 27:26.223
A'ight.

27:26.323 --> 27:27.705
I see what this is.

27:27.805 --> 27:30.067
You got the white pieces.

27:30.167 --> 27:32.469
Opening move is yours.
I'm on the clock.

27:32.569 --> 27:36.553
Tick, tock, tick, tock.

27:36.653 --> 27:38.435
Watch my black ass play.

27:38.535 --> 27:40.758
♪♪

27:40.858 --> 27:43.400
I didn't tell Moses
what you're doing.

27:43.500 --> 27:46.083
Who your new client is.

27:46.183 --> 27:47.765
'Cause I didn't know
what to say.

27:47.865 --> 27:50.247
[Indistinct announcements
over P.A.]

27:50.347 --> 27:53.110
[Cellphone ringing,
indistinct conversations]

27:57.114 --> 27:58.856
Franklin Roberts.

27:58.956 --> 28:00.137
Yo, it's Tweet.

28:00.237 --> 28:02.239
Tweet.

28:04.481 --> 28:06.944
Can you talk?

28:07.044 --> 28:09.627
One hour from now,
around the back of
the liquor store in Roseland.

28:09.727 --> 28:11.308
Okay.

28:11.408 --> 28:14.271
♪♪

28:14.371 --> 28:16.393
-What's up, brah?
-What's up, bro?

28:16.493 --> 28:18.075
Yo, what's up?

28:18.175 --> 28:20.317
Tweet?

28:20.417 --> 28:22.439
What kind of name
is that?

28:22.539 --> 28:25.683
♪♪

28:25.783 --> 28:28.245
He's somebody that can make
a real difference.

28:28.345 --> 28:32.009
♪♪

28:32.109 --> 28:35.572
He came to see me.
Franklin.

28:35.672 --> 28:36.934
Phil: Oh, yeah?

28:37.034 --> 28:38.816
At work.

28:38.916 --> 28:40.257
Wh-What he say?

28:40.357 --> 28:41.899
Told me the pain
was worth it

28:41.999 --> 28:44.501
because he's pulling down
the whole house of cards.

28:44.601 --> 28:46.824
[Chuckles]

28:46.924 --> 28:49.106
Okay. Okay.

28:49.206 --> 28:50.988
Well, anything specific?

28:51.088 --> 28:53.470
♪♪

28:53.570 --> 28:55.993
Said he got hold of
Brannigan's snitch.

28:56.093 --> 28:59.236
♪♪

28:59.336 --> 29:00.878
Okay.

29:00.978 --> 29:02.559
♪♪

29:02.659 --> 29:03.881
Okay.

29:03.981 --> 29:06.403
Oh, but look.

29:06.503 --> 29:09.406
Here.
Come on now.

29:09.506 --> 29:11.929
It's important that the baby
hears what his father loves

29:12.029 --> 29:13.410
before he joins us.

29:13.510 --> 29:16.894
♪ I know, I know, I know,
I know, I know ♪

29:16.994 --> 29:18.335
♪ Yeah ♪

29:18.435 --> 29:19.777
♪ Oh-oh ♪

29:19.877 --> 29:21.658
[Siren chirps]

29:21.758 --> 29:27.464
♪♪

29:27.564 --> 29:29.106
What's up, Tweet?

29:29.206 --> 29:30.908
Let's take a little ride.

29:31.008 --> 29:37.234
♪♪

29:37.334 --> 29:43.480
♪♪

29:43.580 --> 29:46.243
I-I'm down to do
another warrant with y'all.

29:46.343 --> 29:48.565
It'd be cool to get paid
for the last one we did, though.

29:48.665 --> 29:52.770
Ah, look at you, Tweet,
out here hustlin'.

29:52.870 --> 29:54.651
I ain't mad at that.

29:54.751 --> 29:56.493
No worries, bro.
You'll get your money.

29:56.593 --> 29:58.415
That's what's up.

29:58.515 --> 30:02.459
Hey, uh, I heard that, uh, fancy
lawyer was looking for you.

30:02.559 --> 30:04.101
You talk to him?

30:04.201 --> 30:06.103
Nah, I don't mess
with lawyers.

30:06.203 --> 30:07.785
I didn't talk to nobody
like that.

30:07.885 --> 30:09.266
Really?

30:09.366 --> 30:14.551
♪♪

30:14.651 --> 30:16.193
He came by
my old lady's pad,

30:16.293 --> 30:17.434
but I didn't talk
to him, though,

30:17.534 --> 30:19.316
and that's on everything,
for real.

30:19.416 --> 30:21.398
Really?
Yeah.

30:21.498 --> 30:24.321
Give me your phone.

30:24.421 --> 30:26.003
The phone.
Where's your phone?

30:26.103 --> 30:27.885
Get his phone.
Hey, hey!

30:27.985 --> 30:33.090
♪♪

30:33.190 --> 30:35.612
Huh.

30:35.712 --> 30:37.534
Do you recognise
that number, Danny?

30:37.634 --> 30:38.976
Hmm.

30:39.076 --> 30:41.658
Rings a bell with me.

30:41.758 --> 30:44.421
Rings a fucking bell
with me.

30:44.521 --> 30:46.503
Call him.

30:46.603 --> 30:48.786
[Line ringing]

30:48.886 --> 30:51.508
♪♪

30:51.608 --> 30:54.872
[Cellphone ringing]

30:54.972 --> 30:57.394
Tweet?

30:57.494 --> 30:59.156
Tweet?

30:59.256 --> 31:01.959
I'm at the bar, waiting.
Where are you?

31:02.059 --> 31:03.841
Tweet?

31:03.941 --> 31:05.602
Tweet, is that you?

31:05.702 --> 31:06.844
Is that you?

31:06.944 --> 31:08.085
I know that voice.

31:08.185 --> 31:10.808
We all know that voice.

31:10.908 --> 31:12.689
Where we going?

31:12.789 --> 31:21.959
♪♪

31:23.440 --> 31:26.583
I know how hard
this is for you.

31:26.683 --> 31:28.665
Moses gone.

31:28.765 --> 31:30.747
New man in the house.

31:30.847 --> 31:33.230
A little baby
on the way.

31:33.330 --> 31:35.072
We could take a vacation.

31:35.172 --> 31:38.435
Go see Moses, watch him run,
see the ocean.

31:38.535 --> 31:40.077
Joshua?

31:40.177 --> 31:42.179
JoJo.

31:44.901 --> 31:46.683
[Door bangs]

31:46.783 --> 31:52.529
[Indistinct conversations]

31:52.629 --> 31:53.971
Where we going?

31:54.071 --> 31:56.894
We're taking
the scenic route.

31:56.994 --> 31:58.535
[Door slams]

31:58.635 --> 32:02.419
Daily rec.
Inmate rights and privileges.

32:02.519 --> 32:05.782
Nice suicide vest, punk.

32:05.882 --> 32:07.865
[Inmates murmuring, shouting]

32:07.965 --> 32:10.387
Come on, CO,
let me at him.

32:10.487 --> 32:14.151
-I smell bacon up in here.
-Run up on me, punk.

32:14.251 --> 32:17.394
Think we can't get at you
in here, white boy?

32:17.494 --> 32:18.635
Unh! [Spits]

32:18.735 --> 32:20.597
[Inmates shouting]

32:20.697 --> 32:23.520
[Laughter]

32:23.620 --> 32:25.642
Inmate: We're gonna
come for you, pig!

32:25.742 --> 32:33.250
♪♪

32:33.350 --> 32:36.173
Dante:
Now, why GI Joe calling me?

32:36.273 --> 32:38.175
Do you know where I am?

32:38.275 --> 32:40.617
Too bad.

32:40.717 --> 32:42.659
Listen,
I need friends in here,

32:42.759 --> 32:45.342
or I'm gone.

32:45.442 --> 32:47.864
Friendship ain't free.

32:47.964 --> 32:49.746
We'll be in touch.

32:49.846 --> 32:55.192
♪♪

32:55.292 --> 32:57.714
[R&B music playing]

32:57.814 --> 33:00.597
You okay?

33:00.697 --> 33:03.080
Yeah.

33:03.180 --> 33:04.962
It's -- It's my mom.

33:05.062 --> 33:07.124
♪♪

33:07.224 --> 33:09.406
What about her?

33:09.506 --> 33:11.929
She's having a baby.

33:12.029 --> 33:13.690
Wow.

33:13.790 --> 33:15.812
Okay.

33:15.912 --> 33:18.535
You good with that?

33:18.635 --> 33:20.777
[Sighs]

33:20.877 --> 33:22.619
I don't know.
I just feel like --

33:22.719 --> 33:26.303
I feel like my mom
got this wrong.

33:26.403 --> 33:29.426
And I feel like
this guy...

33:29.526 --> 33:32.349
he not right for her.

33:32.449 --> 33:35.272
And now a baby.

33:35.372 --> 33:36.753
Boy or girl?

33:36.853 --> 33:39.716
She don't know.

33:39.816 --> 33:42.439
Heard her say she hope
it's a girl, though.

33:42.539 --> 33:44.121
'Cause girls are better.

33:44.221 --> 33:46.203
Stop it.
[Both laugh]

33:46.303 --> 33:47.684
Girls are better.

33:47.784 --> 33:49.246
Mm, how so?

33:49.346 --> 33:51.128
Say it.

33:51.228 --> 33:53.010
Girls.

33:53.110 --> 33:54.691
Are.

33:54.791 --> 33:56.333
Better.

33:56.433 --> 34:05.422
♪♪

34:05.522 --> 34:07.064
I still ain't say it,
so...

34:07.164 --> 34:09.026
[Scoffs]
Whatever!
[Laughs]

34:09.126 --> 34:11.108
You're so annoying.
Yeah.

34:11.208 --> 34:12.869
[Inmates shouting in distance]

34:12.969 --> 34:14.751
[Cell door bangs]

34:14.851 --> 34:16.853
Eyes on the wall, Logan.

34:17.294 --> 34:19.816
[Wheels rattling]

34:23.500 --> 34:25.582
[Mop squelching]

34:46.203 --> 34:47.784
♪♪

34:47.884 --> 34:49.626
[Conversing indistinctly]

34:49.726 --> 34:50.987
♪♪

34:51.087 --> 34:52.629
[Grunting]

34:52.729 --> 34:54.391
Hey, back up!

34:54.491 --> 34:56.193
-On the wall!
-Hey, hey, hey!

34:56.293 --> 34:57.434
Back up!

34:57.534 --> 35:05.122
♪♪

35:05.222 --> 35:07.244
[Breathing heavily]

35:07.344 --> 35:14.051
♪♪

35:14.151 --> 35:16.133
Tweet: Yo, what you hear
ain't right.

35:16.233 --> 35:18.855
Let's go.
Hands free.

35:18.955 --> 35:28.745
♪♪

35:28.845 --> 35:38.595
♪♪

35:38.695 --> 35:41.158
[Grunting, scuffling]

35:41.258 --> 35:44.321
♪♪

35:44.421 --> 35:46.203
[Tweet choking, gasping]

35:46.303 --> 35:52.008
♪♪

35:52.108 --> 35:57.814
♪♪

35:57.914 --> 36:00.457
[Muffled cries]

36:00.557 --> 36:02.339
I'm sorry, Tweet.

36:02.439 --> 36:06.143
♪♪

36:06.243 --> 36:08.024
[Gasps]

36:08.124 --> 36:14.191
♪♪

36:14.291 --> 36:16.072
[Gurgles]

36:16.172 --> 36:25.322
♪♪

36:25.422 --> 36:27.204
[Body thuds]

36:27.304 --> 36:36.493
♪♪

36:36.593 --> 36:38.375
Let's dress it up.

36:38.475 --> 36:45.882
♪♪

36:47.364 --> 36:50.507
[Breathing heavily]

36:50.607 --> 36:52.929
[Cellphone ringing]

36:55.492 --> 36:58.315
[Sighs]

36:58.415 --> 36:59.956
Hello.

37:00.056 --> 37:01.678
Yes.
Who's speaking?

37:01.778 --> 37:03.320
♪♪

37:03.420 --> 37:05.402
County morgue?

37:05.502 --> 37:06.643
Who?

37:06.743 --> 37:08.805
[Cell door scrapes, bangs]

37:08.905 --> 37:11.408
Make it quick.
I got you covered
for two minutes.

37:11.508 --> 37:18.535
♪♪

37:18.635 --> 37:25.702
♪♪

37:25.802 --> 37:26.943
[Chuckles]

37:27.043 --> 37:28.585
Relax, man.

37:28.685 --> 37:31.107
♪♪

37:31.207 --> 37:32.789
Dante sent me.

37:32.889 --> 37:37.794
♪♪

37:37.894 --> 37:39.916
Complimentary dinner.

37:40.016 --> 37:41.558
It's glass-free.

37:41.658 --> 37:47.444
♪♪

37:47.544 --> 37:49.125
You're welcome.

37:49.225 --> 37:58.535
♪♪

37:58.635 --> 38:01.458
[Paper rustles]

38:01.558 --> 38:02.819
Thank you.

38:02.919 --> 38:05.382
So...

38:05.482 --> 38:08.425
You is like "America's
Most Wanted" in this bitch.

38:08.525 --> 38:11.007
That guard, is he --
He family.

38:13.169 --> 38:15.472
The Nation take care
of its own.

38:15.572 --> 38:17.754
You are not family.

38:17.854 --> 38:21.918
So protection like that,
it's gonna cost you.

38:22.018 --> 38:24.080
I can put something together.
How much am I looking at?

38:24.180 --> 38:25.762
Ten racks.

38:25.862 --> 38:27.564
A week.

38:27.664 --> 38:30.647
I got 10 G's in a duffel bag
behind my bathtub.

38:30.747 --> 38:32.329
I'll give you the address.
Oh, man, you good.

38:32.429 --> 38:34.090
We know where you live.

38:34.190 --> 38:36.613
So, that'll get you
a week.

38:36.713 --> 38:39.416
And your week
started this morning.

38:39.516 --> 38:42.379
You now have the complete
protection of the Nation.

38:42.479 --> 38:46.383
You can eat, you can sleep,
you can sit on this bucket.

38:46.483 --> 38:48.184
I'm gonna be handling
your meal delivery,

38:48.284 --> 38:50.267
so anything that come
through this door

38:50.367 --> 38:54.271
and it ain't in a bag
like that, don't eat it.

38:54.371 --> 38:56.833
You got any problem in here,
no matter how big,

38:56.933 --> 38:59.716
no matter how small,
you ask for Lotty.

38:59.816 --> 39:01.638
You feel me?
I got it.

39:01.738 --> 39:03.480
Hey.

39:03.580 --> 39:05.762
This shit is critical.

39:05.862 --> 39:09.045
You decide you want to step
outside the perimeter

39:09.145 --> 39:10.487
of our agreement,

39:10.587 --> 39:12.969
other forces start
getting involved,

39:13.069 --> 39:14.891
then you on your own,
playboy.

39:14.991 --> 39:16.333
[Banging on door]

39:16.433 --> 39:18.855
[Door scrapes, bangs]

39:18.955 --> 39:21.738
♪♪

39:21.838 --> 39:24.060
[Door scrapes, slams]

39:24.160 --> 39:26.343
♪♪

39:26.443 --> 39:28.224
[Paper rustles]

39:28.324 --> 39:33.790
♪♪

39:33.890 --> 39:39.316
♪♪

39:39.416 --> 39:41.398
[Door scrapes, bangs]

39:41.498 --> 39:43.600
Unit Guard:
Get up, Logan.

39:43.700 --> 39:45.281
Let's go!

39:45.381 --> 39:50.887
♪♪

39:50.987 --> 39:53.169
[Crickets chirping]

39:53.269 --> 40:01.378
♪♪

40:01.478 --> 40:03.480
[Exhales sharply]

40:06.483 --> 40:08.485
Hey, Dad.

40:11.327 --> 40:12.949
300K?

40:13.049 --> 40:16.713
Well, second mortgage
on the house.

40:16.813 --> 40:18.595
The bank worked
with me.

40:18.695 --> 40:19.916
Expedited some things.

40:20.016 --> 40:22.018
Thank you.

40:23.139 --> 40:25.141
Thank you.

40:35.672 --> 40:37.674
I'm sorry.

40:38.555 --> 40:41.858
Well, the person you should
be thanking is your mother.

40:41.958 --> 40:44.140
God rest her soul.

40:44.240 --> 40:46.603
This is what she would've
wanted me to do.

40:48.645 --> 40:52.509
Ah, I tried my damn best
to raise you right,

40:52.609 --> 40:56.873
to put you on the right track,
teach you what matters.

40:56.973 --> 40:58.835
The Logan family...
[scoffs]

40:58.935 --> 41:03.680
...we don't come from much,
but those two things --

41:03.780 --> 41:08.925
honour and loyalty --
it's what defines us.

41:09.025 --> 41:11.127
And you decided to turn
your back on that.

41:11.227 --> 41:14.010
No, it's...

41:14.110 --> 41:17.293
That's -- it's --
it's not like that, Dad.

41:17.393 --> 41:20.837
It's -- It's --
It's more involved.

41:24.120 --> 41:26.543
They're setting me up.

41:26.643 --> 41:28.344
10 bucks.

41:28.444 --> 41:31.307
Bus fare.

41:31.407 --> 41:34.611
And a few things to keep you
clean for a couple of days.

41:38.334 --> 41:40.957
I don't have to
tell you this,

41:41.057 --> 41:44.601
but it's probably not safe
for you to go home

41:44.701 --> 41:46.823
or touch your car
right now.

41:48.585 --> 41:50.587
Dad, I got nobody else.

41:54.230 --> 41:56.232
Well, you'll
figure it out.

41:58.314 --> 42:02.819
Like I said,
I did this for your mother.

42:02.919 --> 42:06.182
But you and me...

42:06.282 --> 42:07.824
we're done.

42:07.924 --> 42:15.151
♪♪

42:15.251 --> 42:17.233
[Engine starts]

42:17.333 --> 42:24.721
♪♪

42:24.821 --> 42:32.208
♪♪

42:32.308 --> 42:35.011
Big fentanyl/heroin
overdose.

42:35.111 --> 42:37.734
Would've gone out happy
and fast.

42:37.834 --> 42:39.375
He had no ID.

42:39.475 --> 42:41.898
Uh, we're lucky they found
your business card on him.

42:41.998 --> 42:51.588
♪♪

42:51.688 --> 43:01.277
♪♪

43:01.377 --> 43:03.600
[Breathing heavily]

43:03.700 --> 43:09.606
♪♪

43:09.706 --> 43:15.672
♪♪

43:16.953 --> 43:26.583
♪♪

43:26.683 --> 43:36.392
♪♪

